President Biden celebrated St. Patrick's Day in the East Room of the White House, delivering a speech and highlighting the strong bond between the United States and Ireland. He shared stories of his Irish heritage and emphasized the importance of unity and cooperation between the two nations. The President also discussed the ongoing issues in Northern Ireland and expressed his commitment to supporting peace and stability in the region. Taoiseach Varadkar, the Prime Minister of Ireland, also spoke at the event, emphasizing the shared values and history between Ireland and the United States. The celebration included musical performances by Niall Horan.